  "prompt": "How can I retrieve my WeChat account if I've forgotten my password, I just linked my linked & I remember I wechat ID.But I don't have QQ/phone linked?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your WeChat password and you do not have QQ or a phone number linked to your account, you can still try the following steps to retrieve your account:\n\n1. **Open WeChat**: Launch the WeChat app on your device.\n\n2. **Tap on 'Log In'**: You'll find the option to log in on the main screen.\n\n3. **Choose 'Forgot Password'**: Look for the \"Forgot Password?\" option, typically located near the password entry field.\n\n4. **Follow the Instructions**: You will be prompted to verify your identity. Since you don\u2019t have a linked phone number or QQ account, look for an option that allows you to use your WeChat ID or email tied to your account.\n\n5. **Account Recovery Options**: If prompted, enter your WeChat ID or other information as instructed. WeChat may send a verification email to any registered email address or provide alternative recovery options.\n\n6. **Contact WeChat Support**: If none of the recovery options work for you, consider reaching out to WeChat's customer service for assistance. Explain your situation and provide any necessary details they might ask for to verify your ownership of the account.\n\n7. **Check Other Linked Accounts**: If you ever linked WeChat with other accounts, like Facebook or other social media, see if you can log in through those platforms.\n\n8. **Be Prepared to Verify Identity**: During the recovery process, be prepared to verify your identity in various ways. This may include answering security questions, providing identification, or verifying recent activity on the account.\n\nKeep in mind that account recovery can take some time, and it's crucial to provide accurate information to expedite the process.",
